    • Class com.github.windsekirun.inappbillingtest.model.Sku extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • productId

          java.lang.String productId
          The product ID for the product.

        • type

          java.lang.String type
          Value must be inapp for an in-app product or subs for subscriptions.

        • price

          java.lang.String price
          Formatted price of the item, including its currency sign. The price does not include tax.

        • priceAmountMicros

          java.lang.String priceAmountMicros
          Price in micro-units, where 1,000,000 micro-units equal one unit of the currency. For example, if price is 7.99, price_amount_micros is 7990000. This value represents the localized, rounded price for a particular currency.

        • priceCurrencyCode

          java.lang.String priceCurrencyCode
          ISO 4217 currency code for price. For example, if price is specified in British pounds sterling, price_currency_code is GBP.

        • title

          java.lang.String title
          Title of the product.

        • description

          java.lang.String description
          Description of the product.

        • dataSignature

          java.lang.String dataSignature
          Signature of Purchase, BASE64 encoded

    • Class com.github.windsekirun.inappbillingtest.model.Transaction extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • autoRenewing

          java.lang.String autoRenewing
          Indicates whether the subscription renews automatically. If true, the subscription is active, and will automatically renew on the next billing date. If false, indicates that the user has canceled the subscription. The user has access to subscription content until the next billing date and will lose access at that time unless they re-enable automatic renewal (or manually renew, as described in Manual Renewal). If you offer a grace period, this value remains set to true for all subscriptions, as long as the grace period has not lapsed. The next billing date is extended dynamically every day until the end of the grace period or until the user fixes their payment method.

        • orderId

          java.lang.String orderId
          A unique order identifier for the transaction. This identifier corresponds to the Google payments order ID. If the order is a test purchase made through the In-app Billing Sandbox, orderId is blank.

        • packageName

          java.lang.String packageName
          The application package from which the purchase originated.

        • productId

          java.lang.String productId
          The item's product identifier. Every item has a product ID, which you must specify in the application's product list on the Google Play developer console.

        • purchaseTime

          long purchaseTime
          The time the product was purchased, in milliseconds since the epoch (Jan 1, 1970).

        • purchaseState

          int purchaseState
          The purchase state of the order. Possible values are 0 (purchased), 1 (canceled), or 2 (refunded).

        • developerPayload

          java.lang.String developerPayload
          A developer-specified string that contains supplemental information about an order. You can specify a value for this field when you make a getBuyIntent request.

        • purchaseToken

          java.lang.String purchaseToken
          A token that uniquely identifies a purchase for a given item and user pair.

        • purchaseInfo

          java.lang.String purchaseInfo
          Full-string of Transaction

        • dataSignature

          java.lang.String dataSignature
